                                         CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating a murder case in Dutywa after a tavern owner was shot dead.  Authorities believe three people who had pretended to be customers attacked the man on Saturday night.  The police’s Jackson Manatha says the suspects then fled the scene. “While he was assisting them, one of the suspects drew his firearm and fatally shot the 47-year-old man on his upper body. They also robbed him of his cellphone and an undisclosed amount of money. At this point in time, no one has been arrested.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)